{"article_id":"QvhlZ6UBkDutV5Il","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Republicans powered Justice Brett M. Kavanaugh through the Senate this weekend ,","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"but not before lawmakers said","depth":8},{"id":2,"text":"they had hit \" rock bottom \"","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"with the poisonous atmosphere","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"pervading the Capitol ,","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"leaving all sides fearful about what happens","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"the next time","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"they are asked to confirm a Supreme Court nominee .","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"Republican leaders said","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"they hoped","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"the 50-48 vote","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"to confirm Justice Kavanaugh","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"would be a cleansing moment ,","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"sending a signal","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"that the nastiness of the past few months wasn ' t a successful strategy for Democrats","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"trying to sink a nominee","depth":11},{"id":16,"text":"whose legal credentials were stellar .","depth":11},{"id":17,"text":"\" A vote","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"to confirm Judge Kavanaugh today","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"is a vote","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"to end this brief , dark chapter in the Senate ' s history","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"and turn the page toward a brighter tomorrow , \"","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"said Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell , Kentucky Republican .","depth":7},{"id":23,"text":"Mr. McConnell managed to shepherd Justice Kavanaugh through the Senate with the slimmest of majorities in a hostile media environment and with an election looming in a month .","depth":6},{"id":24,"text":"Hours after Saturday ' s vote , President Trump signed Justice Kavanaugh ' s commission","depth":5},{"id":25,"text":"and Chief Justice John G. Roberts Jr. administered the oath of office ,","depth":5},{"id":26,"text":"putting the court back at its full contingent of nine justices .","depth":4},{"id":27,"text":"Democrats complained","depth":7},{"id":28,"text":"that Republicans broke traditions on access to documents","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"- millions of pages of records from Justice Kavanaugh ' s time in the Bush White House went unexamined -","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"and on the nature of background checks .","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"They also were disappointed","depth":7},{"id":32,"text":"that the FBI failed to corroborate 36-year-old accusations of sexual assault .","depth":7},{"id":33,"text":"Democrats also said","depth":6},{"id":34,"text":"Justice Kavanaugh lowered the bar with his angry testimony last month ,","depth":7},{"id":35,"text":"when he sparred with senators","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"who accused him of lying , attempted rape , using crude language and drinking as a teenager .","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"Republicans complained of a massive liberal public relations machine","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"that worked overtime","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"to fabricate erroneous stories about the judge ' s 12 years of rulings ,","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"concocted conspiracy theories","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"about why he was nominated ,","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"and then maltreated Christine Blasey Ford ,","depth":12},{"id":43,"text":"who lodged the first misconduct allegations against Justice Kavanaugh privately ,","depth":12},{"id":44,"text":"only to see them leaked .","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"Sen. Jack Reed , a Rhode Island Democrat with more than two decades in the Senate , said","depth":8},{"id":46,"text":"both sides were to blame ,","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"with Republicans escalating matters .","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"\" Without some major change in the power of the majority ,","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"I hope","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"there is no illusion among my colleagues","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"that we have endured over the last few weeks , if anything , the beginning of what is to come , \"","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"he said .","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"Sen. Thom Tillis , a North Carolina Republican","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"who as a member of the Judiciary Committee had an up-close look at the past month ' s circus ,","depth":8},{"id":55,"text":"cautioned Republicans not to stoop to the same tactics","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"the next time","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"a Democratic president gets the chance","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"to make a nomination .","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"\" If Republicans ever decide to emulate the Democrats ' ' search and destroy ' playbook ,","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"they can count me out .","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"Doing so would stoop Congress to a level","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"we should never see again , \"","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"he said .","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"On that count , he is battling history ,","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"which has proved","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"that each new low","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"set by one party","depth":11},{"id":68,"text":"is quickly embraced by the other .","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"Republicans said","depth":5},{"id":70,"text":"they were following the lead of former Sen. Joseph R. Biden , Delaware Democrat ,","depth":6},{"id":71,"text":"when they refused to consider President Obama ' s 2016 nomination of Judge Merrick Garland to the Supreme Court ,","depth":7},{"id":72,"text":"holding the seat open","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"for the next president","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"to fill .","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"When Democrats pioneered the partisan filibuster of judicial nominees under President George W. Bush ,","depth":6},{"id":76,"text":"Republicans did the same for Mr. Obama .","depth":6},{"id":77,"text":"In 2013 , Democrats triggered the \" nuclear option \"","depth":7},{"id":78,"text":"changing the interpretation of the rules","depth":8},{"id":79,"text":"to defang the filibuster for most judicial nominees .","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"Republicans followed last year","depth":7},{"id":81,"text":"and expanded the nuclear option","depth":8},{"id":82,"text":"for use on Supreme Court picks .","depth":8},{"id":83,"text":"Senate Minority Leader Charles E. Schumer , New York Democrat , was asked last week","depth":5},{"id":84,"text":"whether he would try to reverse that change","depth":7},{"id":85,"text":"and restore the filibuster ' s power for Supreme Court nominees","depth":7},{"id":86,"text":"if Democrats take control of the chamber .","depth":6},{"id":87,"text":"He was noncommittal .","depth":5},{"id":88,"text":"\" The bottom line is that the Republican leader moved it down to","depth":8},{"id":89,"text":"[ 50 ] .","depth":8},{"id":90,"text":"The bottom line is we ' ll have to look at that","depth":8},{"id":91,"text":"should we get back into the majority , \"","depth":8},{"id":92,"text":"he said .","depth":6},{"id":93,"text":"Still , Mr. McConnell was optimistic","depth":6},{"id":94,"text":"that the Senate can recover .","depth":6},{"id":95,"text":"Even during the Kavanaugh fight ,","depth":7},{"id":96,"text":"he said ,","depth":7},{"id":97,"text":"the Senate wrote and approved two massive spending bills ,","depth":7},{"id":98,"text":"cleared an anti-opioid package","depth":8},{"id":99,"text":"and made headway on other bipartisan priorities .","depth":8},{"id":100,"text":"Those sorts of accomplishments rely on the relationships","depth":6},{"id":101,"text":"senators build up over decades ,","depth":6},{"id":102,"text":"and there was evidence , even amid the strife ,","depth":6},{"id":103,"text":"that the relationships remain strong .","depth":6},{"id":104,"text":"Minutes after Senate Minority Whip Richard J. Durbin , Illinois Democrat , attacked Sen. Chuck Grassley , Iowa Republican and chairman of the Judiciary Committee , for his handling of the Kavanaugh nomination ,","depth":3},{"id":105,"text":"Mr. Durbin crossed the aisle","depth":4},{"id":106,"text":"to exchange handshakes and a few chuckles with Mr. Grassley .","depth":4}],"relations":[{"parent":213,"left":189,"right":212,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":189,"left":133,"right":188,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":133,"left":130,"right":132,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":130,"left":114,"right":129,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":114,"left":0,"right":113,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":113,"left":110,"right":112,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":110,"left":108,"right":109,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":108,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":109,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":112,"left":5,"right":111,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":111,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":129,"left":122,"right":128,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":122,"left":8,"right":121,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":121,"left":9,"right":120,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":120,"left":116,"right":119,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":116,"left":115,"right":12,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":115,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":119,"left":13,"right":118,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":118,"left":14,"right":117,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":117,"left":15,"right":16,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":128,"left":127,"right":23,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":127,"left":126,"right":22,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":126,"left":123,"right":125,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":123,"left":17,"right":18,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{